--
-- Table structure for table `act_effect_item`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `act_effect_item`;
CREATE TABLE `act_effect_item` (
  `ACT_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `ACT_EFFECT_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `RAT` decimal(6,5) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_ITEM_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`ACT_ID`,`ACT_EFFECT_IX`),
  KEY `IS_SPECIFIED_IN2` (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`),
  KEY `REF112105` (`ACT_ID`,`ACT_EFFECT_IX`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_SPECIFIED_IN2` FOREIGN KEY (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`) REFERENCES `obj_item` (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFACT_EFFECT105` FOREIGN KEY (`ACT_ID`, `ACT_EFFECT_IX`) REFERENCES `act_effect` (`ACT_ID`, `ACT_EFFECT_IX`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

  KEY `IS_DETAILED_THROUGH` (`ACT_EVENT_ID`),
  KEY `PROVIDES_APPLIC_INFO38` (`RPTD_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK390` (`CLSFC_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK391` (`CRIME_IND_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK390` FOREIGN KEY (`CLSFC_CODE`) REFERENCES `act_event_det_clsfc_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK391` FOREIGN KEY (`CRIME_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `act_event_det_crime_indic_code` (`CODE`),

  CONSTRAINT `REFROE10` FOREIGN KEY (`ROE_ID`) REFERENCES `roe` (`ROE_ID`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Table structure for table `act_task_stat`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `act_task_stat`;
CREATE TABLE `act_task_stat` (
  `ACT_TASK_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `ACT_TASK_STAT_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `COMPL_RAT` decimal(6,5) default NULL,
  `PLANNING_IND_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `PROGRESS_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `AMEND_TIMING_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `RPTD_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`ACT_TASK_ID`,`ACT_TASK_STAT_IX`),
  KEY `PROVIDES_APPLIC_INFO9` (`RPTD_ID`),
  KEY `HAS3` (`ACT_TASK_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK294` (`PLANNING_IND_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK295` (`AMEND_TIMING_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK296` (`CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK297` (`PROGRESS_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK294` FOREIGN KEY (`PLANNING_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `act_task_stat_planning_ind_cd` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK295` FOREIGN KEY (`AMEND_TIMING_CODE`) REFERENCES `act_task_stat_amend_timing_cd` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK296` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `act_task_stat_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK297` FOREIGN KEY (`PROGRESS_CODE`) REFERENCES `act_task_stat_progress_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `HAS3` FOREIGN KEY (`ACT_TASK_ID`) REFERENCES `act_task` (`ACT_TASK_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `PROVIDES_APPLIC_INFO9` FOREIGN KEY (`RPTD_ID`) REFERENCES `rptd` (`RPTD_ID`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Table structure for table `anchr`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `anchr`;
CREATE TABLE `anchr` (
  `ANCHR_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `BOTTOM_TYPE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `DAY_LIMIT_NET_EXPL_QTY` decimal(6,0) default NULL,
  `DRAUGHT_HIGH_TIDE_DIM` decimal(12,3) default NULL,
  `DRAUGHT_LOW_TIDE_DIM` decimal(12,3) default NULL,
  `MOORINGS_TYPE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `NIGHT_LIMIT_NET_EXPL_QTY` decimal(6,0) default NULL,
  `PRVL_WIND_DIR_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `VESSEL_TONG_QTY` decimal(9,0) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`ANCHR_ID`),
  KEY `REF97555` (`ANCHR_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK123` (`BOTTOM_TYPE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK124` (`PRVL_WIND_DIR_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK125` (`MOORINGS_TYPE_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK123` FOREIGN KEY (`BOTTOM_TYPE_CODE`) REFERENCES `anchr_bottom_type_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK124` FOREIGN KEY (`PRVL_WIND_DIR_CODE`) REFERENCES `dir_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK125` FOREIGN KEY (`MOORINGS_TYPE_CODE`) REFERENCES `anchr_moorings_type_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFFAC555` FOREIGN KEY (`ANCHR_ID`) REFERENCES `fac` (`FAC_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

An area of low atmospheric pressure that has a closed circulation that is cyclonic, i.e., as viewed from above, the circulation is counterclockwise in the Northern Hemisphere, clockwise in the Southern Hemisphere, undefined at the Equator. Because cyclonic circulation and relatively low atmospheric pressure usually coexist, in common practice the terms cyclone and low are used interchangeably. Also, because cyclones often are accompanied by inclement (sometimes destructive) weather, they are frequently referred to simply as storms. 2. Frequently misused to denote a tornado. 3. In the Indian Ocean, a tropical cyclone of hurricane or typhoon force.'),('OCCFRT','Occluded front','The line along which a cold front has overtaken a warm front at ground level.'),('RDGLIN','Ridge Line','An elongated region of high atmospheric pressure.'),('SQLLIN','Squall Line','A line of high winds and thunderstorms in convectively unstable air, an instability line (of non-frontal nature); it may be generated by a cold front.'),('STAFRT','Stationary Front','A situation in which the surface position of a front does not move; the flow on either side of such a boundary is nearly parallel to the position of the front.'),('TRGLIN','Trough Line','An elongated region of low atmospheric pressure.'),('UPCFRT','Upper Cold Front','Occurs when discontinuity at the forward edge of an advancing cold air mass is displacing warmer air in its path and the two air masses intersect above ground level.'),('UPWFRT','Upper Warm Front','Occurs when discontinuity at the forward edge of an advancing warm air mass is displacing cooler air in its path and the two air masses intersect above ground level.'),('WRMFRT','Warm Front','The discontinuity at the forward edge of an advancing warm air mass that is displacing cooler air in its path.'),('343','LINES',NULL),('368','Jet Stream',NULL);

-- Table structure for table `cbrn_event`

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `cbrn_event`;
CREATE TABLE `cbrn_event` (
  `CBRN_EVENT_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `SUBCAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `ALARM_RESULT_IND_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CONF_TEST_IND_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `MAT_CNTR_TYPE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `MAT_CNTR_TOTAL_CNT` decimal(4,0) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`CBRN_EVENT_ID`),
  KEY `REF69365` (`CBRN_EVENT_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK26` (`CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK27` (`SUBCAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK28` (`ALARM_RESULT_IND_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK29` (`CONF_TEST_IND_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK30` (`MAT_CNTR_TYPE_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK26` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `cbrn_event_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK27` FOREIGN KEY (`SUBCAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `cbrn_event_subcat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK28` FOREIGN KEY (`ALARM_RESULT_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `cbrn_event_alrm_rsult_ind_cd` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK29` FOREIGN KEY (`CONF_TEST_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `cbrn_event_conf_test_ind_cd` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK30` FOREIGN KEY (`MAT_CNTR_TYPE_CODE`) REFERENCES `cbrn_event_mat_cntr_type_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFACT_EVENT365` FOREIGN KEY (`CBRN_EVENT_ID`) REFERENCES `act_event` (`ACT_EVENT_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

INSERT INTO `cbrn_event_mat_cntr_type_code` VALUES ('BML','Bomblets','A small munition capable of containing a biological warfare agent'),('BOM','Bomb','A case filled with explosive, inflammable material, poison gas, or smoke, etc., dropped from aircraft, or thrown or deposited by hand.'),('BTL','Pressurized gas bottle','A large metal cylinder holding liquefied gas under pressure.'),('BUK','Bunker','No definition provided in ATP-45(B).'),('CON','Generic storage container','A receptacle in which material is held or carried.'),('DRM','Nominal 200 litre storage drum','A cylindrical container that holds 200 litres.'),('GEN','Generator (aerosol)','An instrument or machine capable of releasing a substance as a fine spray by subjecting it to pressure.'),('MNE','Mine (NBC filled only)','A mine containing a chemical or radiological agent designed to kill, injure, or incapacitate personnel or to contaminate materiel or terrain.'),('MSL','Missile','A weapon that is self-propelled or directed by remote control, carrying conventional or nuclear explosive.'),('NKN','Not known','It is not possible to determine which value is most applicable.'),('RCT','Reactor','A facility that contains a controlled nuclear fission chain reaction. It can be used to generate electricity, conduct research, and produce isotopes and manmade elements such as plutonium.'),('RKT','Rocket','A cylindrical projectile that can be propelled to a great height or distance by the combustion of its contents.'),('SHL','Shell','An explosive artillery projectile or bomb.'),('SPR','Spray (tank)','A container used to dispense chemical or biological agents.'),('STK','Stockpile','No definition provided in ATP-45(B).'),('TNK','Tank','A large receptacle or storage chamber, especially for liquid or gas.'),('TOR','Torpedo','A cigar-shaped self-propelled underwater missile designed to be fired from a ship, submarine, or an aircraft.'),('WST','Waste','A container of wastes that includes materials such as laboratory wastes and protective clothing.');
UNLOCK TABLES;

--
-- Table structure for table `cfeat_stat`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `cfeat_stat`;
CREATE TABLE `cfeat_stat` (
  `CFEAT_STAT_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `INVSTG_STAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CBRN_THREAT_LVL_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `SECURITY_STAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `USAGE_STAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`CFEAT_STAT_ID`,`OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX`),
  KEY `REF178268` (`CFEAT_STAT_ID`,`OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX`),
  KEY `CONFK343` (`INVSTG_STAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK344` (`SECURITY_STAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK345` (`CBRN_THREAT_LVL_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK346` (`USAGE_STAT_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK343` FOREIGN KEY (`INVSTG_STAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `cfeat_stat_invstg_stat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK344` FOREIGN KEY (`SECURITY_STAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `cfeat_stat_security_stat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK345` FOREIGN KEY (`CBRN_THREAT_LVL_CODE`) REFERENCES `cfeat_stat_cbrn_threat_lvl_cd` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK346` FOREIGN KEY (`USAGE_STAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `usage_status_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFOBJ_ITEM_STAT268` FOREIGN KEY (`CFEAT_STAT_ID`, `OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX`) REFERENCES `obj_item_stat` (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`, `OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `cfeat_stat`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `cfeat_stat` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `cfeat_stat` WRITE;
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `cfeat_stat` ENABLE KEYS */;

INSERT INTO `cfeat_type_cat_code` VALUES ('AAXIS','Air axis of advance','A general air corridor of advance, which extends towards the enemy. It follows an axis suitable for the airmobile force to which the axis was assigned. An air axis of advance does not directly control or use terrain.'),('ACCPOS','Aircraft control position','No definition provided in ADatP-3 Baseline 11.'),('ADACAR','Air defence action area','An area and the airspace above it within which friendly aircraft or surface-to-air weapons are normally given precedence in operations except under specified conditions.'),('ADAREA','Air defence area','An area and the airspace above it within which procedures are established to minimize mutual interference between air force and land based/army air defence and other operations.'),('ADIDZN','Air defence identification zone','Airspace within which ready identification, location, and control of airborne vehicles are required.'),('ADOPAR','Air defence operations area','An area and airspace above it within which procedures are established to minimize mutual interference between maritime and amphibious air defence and other operations.'),('AIMPT','Aim point','The point to which a weapon is targeted.'),('AIRCAR','Airspace control area','Airspace which is laterally defined by boundaries of the area of operations.'),('AIRCOA','Airspace coordination area','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that is a three-dimensional block of airspace in a target area, established by the appropriate ground commander, in which friendly aircraft are reasonably safe from friendly surface fire. Normally it is the area seized in the assault phase of an airborne or air assault operation. Army--The airhead contains enough drop zones (DZs), landing zones (LZs), and extraction zones (EZs) to ensure mass, interior lines of communication and defence in depth.'),('AIRRFL','Air-to-air refuelling area','Airspace of defined dimensions set aside for air-to-air refuelling operations, excluding special operation forces air-to-air missions.'),('ALRTAR','Alert area','Airspace which may contain a high volume of pilot training activities or an unusual type of aerial activity, neither of which is hazardous to aircraft.'),('ALTRAR','Altitude reservation area','Block of altitude, normally medium to high, reserved for aircraft to transit or loiter within the Force Air Coordination Area (FACA) for mission accomplishment.'),('AMBEXP','Ambulance exchange point','A location where a patient is transferred from one ambulance to another en-route to a medical treatment facility. An axis of advance symbol graphically portrays a commander’s intention, such as avoidance of built-up areas or envelopment of an enemy force. It follows terrain suitable for the size of the force to which the axis was assigned, and is often a road, a group of roads, or a designated series of locations. An axis of advance is not used to direct the control of terrain or the clearance of enemy forces from specific locations. Intermediate objectives are normally assigned for these purposes.'),('BASDZN','Base defence zone','A zone established around airbases to enhance the effectiveness of local ground based air defence systems.'),('BATPOS','Battle position','[No definition provided in APP-6A]'),('BCHH','Beachhead','A designated area on a hostile shore which, when seized and held, ensures the continuous landing of troops and materiel, and provides manoeuvre space requisite for subsequent projected operations ashore. A line which delineates surface areas (or airspace) for the purpose of facilitating coordination and deconfliction of operations between adjacent units, formations or areas. 2. A control measure normally drawn along identifiable terrain features and used to delineate areas of tactical responsibility between adjacent units and between higher headquarters to the rear of the subordinate units. Control measures which define the left and right limits of a unit\'s zone of action or sector. Together with the rear and forward boundary and a coordinating altitude, lateral boundaries define the area of operations for a commander.'),('BDYPOA','Boundary, political/administrative','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE with a line location by which political or administrative areas of responsibility are defined.'),('BDYPT','Boundary point','A point on a boundary.'),('BERLIN','Bearing line','[No definition given in APP-6A]'),('BIOCTM','Biologically contaminated area','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that identifies the predicted or confirmed contour of an area in which biological agents may produce casualties in man or animals and damage to plants or materiel.'),('BLOPOS','Blocking position','A defensive position so sited as to deny the enemy access to a given area or to prevent his advance in a given direction.'),('BOMBAR','Bomb area','[No definition given in APP-6A]'),('BOUNDR','Boundary, airspace','The lateral limits of an airspace control area, airspace control sub-area, high-density airspace control zone or airspace restricted area.'),('BRDGH','Bridgehead','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE with an area location held or to be gained on the enemy\'s side of a water obstacle. Army-In river-crossing operations, an area on the enemy\'s side of the water obstacle that is large enough to accommodate the majority of the crossing force and that has adequate terrain to permit defence of the crossing sites, and that provides a base for continuing the attack.'),('BRKUPP','Break-up point','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that identifies a point where aircraft split up during a mission.'),('BUFRZN','Buffer zone','Airspace designed specifically to provide a buffer between various airspace control measures.'),('BULEYE','Bullseye','An established reference point from which the position of an object can be references by bearing (Magnetic) and range (in nautical miles NM) from this point.'),('CBRNHA','CBRN attack and hazard area','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that identifies the predicted or confirmed contour of the NBC (CBRN) hazard area.'),('CBRNRS','CBRN reading/sample/detection','The point at which a reading, sample or detection of an NBC (CBRN) contaminant is performed.'),('CFL','Coordination fire line','A line beyond which conventional surface fire support may fire at any time within the area of operations of the establishing headquarters without additional coordination. location which defines the rear part of theatre of operations (behind but contiguous to the combat zone) which contains the lines of communication, establishments for supply and evacuation, and other agencies required for the immediate support and maintenance of the field forces.'),('CONCA','Concentration area','An area, usually in the theatre of operations, where troops are assembled before slow and fast moving air traffic at low level.'),('CRCNZN','Carrier control zone','Area around a ship operating fixed/rotary wing aircraft.'),('CRDALT','Coordinating altitude','A procedural airspace The coordinating altitude is normally specified in the airspace control plan and may include a buffer zone for small altitude deviations.'),('CRDPNT','Coordinating point','Designated point at which, in all types of combat, adjacent units/formations must make contact for purposes of control and coordination. Army--A control measure that indicates a specific location for the coordination of fires and manoeuvre between adjacent units. They usually are indicated whenever a boundary crosses the forward battle area (FEBA), and may be indicated when a boundary crosses phase lines (PLs) used to control security forces.'),('CRSBAR','Cross-border area','A temporary segregated area established over international boundaries for specific operational requirements.'),('CRSVZN','Crossover zone','The airspace beyond the maritime Missile Engagement Zone (MEZ) that may be entered by Combat Air Patrol (CAP) aircraft when in hot pursuit in order to complete an interception.'),('CTLPNT','Control point','A position along a route of march at which men are stationed to give information and instructions for the regulation of supply or traffic.'),('CZ','Combat zone','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE with an area location that denotes the area required by combat forces for the conduct of operations.'),('DA','Direction of attack','A specific direction or assigned route a force must use to draw the enemy\'s attention away from the location of the commanders decisive operation. Forces conducting a feint make direct fire contact with the enemy.'),('DECPNT','Decision point','An event, area, line, or point in the battlespace where tactical decisions are required resulting from the wargaming process or the operations order. Decision points do not dictate commander\'s decisions, they only indicate that a decision is required, and they indicate when/where the decision should be made to have the maximum effect on friendly or enemy courses of action.'),('DEFPOS','Defensive position','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that is used in planning to designate a belt of terrain, generally parallel to the front, which includes two or more organised, or partially organised, battle positions.'),('DEFZ','Defence zone','The area extending from the forward edge of the battle area to its rear boundary.'),('DMPI','Desired mean point of impact','The point at which a projectile, bomb, or re-entry vehicle is expected to impact.'),('DNGRAR','Danger area','An airspace of defined dimensions within which activities dangerous to the flight of aircraft may exist at specified times.'),('DNPKPT','Downed aircrew pickup point','A point to where aviators will attempt to evade and escape to be recovered by friendly forces.'),('DPBSLN','Deep battle synchronisation line','The forward boundary of the ground component commander\'s (GCC) area of operation. The DBSL defines the geographic areas of responsibility of the GCC and air component commander.'),('DROPPT','Drop point','[No definition given in APP-6A]'),('DZ','Drop zone','A specific area upon which airborne troops, equipment, or supplies are airdropped by parachute. NOTE:  This zone can include one or more drop sites.'),('EA','Engagement area','An area where the commander intends to contain and destroy an enemy force with the massed fires of all available weapons.'),('ELCCAR','Electronic combat area','Airspace established specifically for airborne platforms engaging in electronic combat.'),('ENCRCL','Encirclement','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE with an area location to indicate the loss of freedom of manoeuvre to one force resulting from an enemy force\'s control of all routes of egress and reinforcement.'),('ENDARP','End aerial refuelling point','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that identifies the point that marks the end of a straight-line segment along which a tanker aircraft offloads fuel to a receiving aircraft.'),('ENDMPT','End of mission point','The mission will terminate at the specific point.'),('ENDRPT','End of route point','Identifies the end point of a route.'),('ENGREG','Engineer regulating point','Checkpoint to ensure that vehicles do not exceed the capacity of the crossing means and to give drivers final instructions on site-specific procedures and information, such as speed and vehicle interval.'),('ENTL','Entry line','The line bounding a controlled area (such as crossing area) that controls entry to that area.'),('ENTPT','Entry point','A point designated for use by vehicles or personnel in entering an area, line or volume.'),('ENTRGT','Entry gate','The point to which an aircraft will be directed to commence the transit inbound from an airfield or force at sea.'),('EXITGT','Exit gate','The point to which an aircraft will be directed to commence the transit outbound from an airfield or force at sea.'),('EXITPT','Exit point','A point designated for use by vehicles or personnel in leaving an area, line or volume.'),('EXTZON','Extraction zone','A specified drop zone used for the delivery of equipment and/or supplies by means of an extraction technique from an aircraft flying very close to the ground.'),('FALRAR','Falcon radials area','Planned magnetic bearings along which aircraft depart and return to ships.'),('FARRFP','Forward arming and refuelling point','A point designated by a deployed aviation commander that permits combat aircraft to rapidly refuel and rearm simultaneously.'),('FCZ','Forward combat zone','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE with an area location compromising the territory forward of the corps rear boundary.'),('FEBA','Forward edge of the battle area','The foremost limits of a series of areas in which ground combat units are deployed, excluding the areas in which the covering or screening forces are operating, designated to coordinate fire support, the positioning of forces, or the manoeuvre of units.'),('FEZ','Fighter engagement zone','a. In maritime usage, the airspace beyond the crossover zone out to limits defined by the officer in tactical command, in which fighters have freedom of action to identify and engage air targets. b. In air defence, airspace of defined dimensions within which the responsibility for engagement of air threats normally rests with a fighter aircraft.'),('FINAPF','Final approach fix','The point in a non-precision approach where the final approach normally begins.'),('FIRING','Fire position area','The specific location within an Artillery area CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE from which a fire unit delivers fire.'),('FIRUMB','Fire umbrella','The airspace over a naval force at sea within the fire of ships\' anti-aircraft weapons can endanger aircraft, and within which special procedures are established for identification and operation of friendly aircraft.'),('FLINRG','Flight information region','An airspace of defined dimensions within which flight information service and alerting service are provided.'),('FLT','Forward line of troops','A line that indicates the most forward positions of forces in any kind of military operation at a specific time. It normally identifies the forward location of covering and screening forces. Army--The FLOT may be at, beyond, or short of the FEBA.'),('FNCOLN','Final coordination line','A line close to the enemy position used to coordinate the lifting and/or shifting of supporting fires with the final deployment of manoeuvre elements. It should be recognisable on the ground. It is not a fire support coordination measure.'),('FNPRFR','Final protective fire','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that is an immediately available prearranged barrier of fire designed to impede enemy movement across defensive lines or areas.'),('FOACAR','Force air coordination area','An area surrounding a force within which air coordination measures are required to prevent mutual interference between all friendly surface and air units and their weapon systems.'),('FOOPLN','Forward operating location','An advanced position, usually of a temporary nature, from which air or ground units operate.'),('FREFIR','Free fire area','A specific designated area into which any weapon system may fire without additional coordination with the establishing headquarters. Normally, it is established on identifiable terrain by division or higher headquarters.'),('FRUPPL','Forming up place','The last position occupied by the assault echelon before crossing the start line/line of departure.'),('FSCL','Fire support coordination line','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE with an area location that is established and adjusted by appropriate land or amphibious force commanders within their boundaries in consultation with superior, subordinate, supporting, and affected commanders. Fire support coordination lines (FSCLs) facilitate the expeditious attack of surface targets of opportunity beyond the coordinating measure.'),('FWDZON','Forward area air defence zone','A specifically defined air space in the combat zone for which air defence must be planned and provided.'),('GENARE','General area','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that identifies an area defined by a higher commander within which the subordinate must accomplish his mission and protect his forces. It applies to both land and naval forces.'),('HAMZON','High altitude missile engagement zone','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that identifies the airspace of defined dimensions within which the responsibility for engagement of air threats normally rests with high-altitude surface-to-air missiles.'),('HAZARD','Hazard area','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that identifies the predicted contour of an area in which unprotected personnel may be affected by the release of a hazardous material spreading from its point of release.'),('HDAZON','High density airspace control zone','Airspace designated in an airspace control plan or airspace control order in which there is a concentrated employment of numerous and varied weapons and airspace users. A high-density airspace control zone has defined dimensions that usually coincide with geographical features or navigational aids. Access to a high-density airspace control zone is normally controlled by the manoeuvre commander. The manoeuvre commander can also direct a more restrictive weapons status within the high-density airspace control zone.'),('HIDE','Hide','An area in which a force conceals itself before operations or before moving into battle position.'),('HNDVGT','Hand over gate','A point at which the control of the aircraft, if radar hand over is used, changes from one controller to another.'),('HOLDLN','Holding line','In retrograde river-crossing operations, the outer limit of the area established between the enemy and the water obstacle to preclude direct and observed indirect fires into crossing areas.'),('IDSFPT','Identification safety point','A point at which aircraft, on joining a maritime force, will attempt to establish two-way communications with the surface force and commence identification procedures.'),('IFFOFF','Identification Friend Foe switch off line','Line demarking where friendly aircraft enroute to targets stop emitting an Identification-Friend-Foe incident has occurred.'),('INFLIN','Infiltration line','An infiltration lane is a control measure that fixes fire planning responsibilities and coordinates forward and lateral movement of infiltrating units.'),('INIAPF','Initial approach fix','The point in an instrument approach that the aircraft has departed and is manoeuvring to enter the intermediate or final approach.'),('INITPT','Initial point','A well-defined point, easily distinguishable visually and/or electronically, used as a starting point for a weapons or reconnaissance run on a target.'),('INTOBJ','Intermediate objective','An area or feature between the line of departure and an objective that must be seized and/or held.'),('ISR','Identification safety range','Minimum range to which an aircraft may close to a maritime force without having been positively identified as friendly.'),('JEZ','Joint engagement zone','In air defence, that airspace of defined dimensions within which multiple air defence systems (surface-to-air missiles and aircraft) are simultaneously employed to engage air threats.'),('JNTOAR','Joint operations area','Area of land, sea, and airspace defined by a combat commander or subordinate unified commander, in which joint force commander conducts military operations to accomplish a specific mission.'),('KEYTER','Key terrain','Any locality, or area, the seizure of which affords a marked advantage to either combatant.'),('KILBOX','Kill box','A volume of airspace where fighter aircraft operate in a weapons free mode and can use their weapons in beyond line of sight operations.'),('KILLA','Killing area','A zone in which a commander plans to force the enemy to concentrate so as to destroy him.'),('LA','Landing area','The part of the objective area within which are equipment the area is impassable. Note - this definition does not identify whether it is a procedural issue, limitation or a trafficability issue.'),('LNKPPT','Linkup point','A CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE with an easily recognisable point location on the ground where two forces conducting a linkup meet. When one force is stationary, linkup points normally are established where the moving force\'s routes of advance intersect the stationary force\'s security elements. Linkup points for two moving forces are established on boundaries where the two forces are expected to converge.'),('LNMEZN','Land missile engagement zone','In land-based air defence, an airspace of defined dimensions within which the responsibility for engagement normally rests with the surface based air defence systems. A main axis of advance symbol graphically portrays a commander’s intention for the main elements of his force, such as avoidance of built-up areas or envelopment of an enemy force. It follows terrain suitable for the size of the force to which the axis was assigned, and is often a road, a group of roads, or a designated series of locations. An axis of advance is not used to direct the control of terrain or the clearance of enemy forces from specific locations. Intermediate objectives are normally assigned for these purposes.'),('MEZ','Missile engagement zone, general','In air defence, that airspace of defined dimensions within which the responsibility for engagement of air threats normally rests with short-range air defence weapons.   CONSTRAINT `CONFK36` FOREIGN KEY (`RELEASE_CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `release_category_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK37` FOREIGN KEY (`SPILL_SIZE_CODE`) REFERENCES `chm_bio_event_spill_size_code` (`CODE`),

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `cone_vol`;
CREATE TABLE `cone_vol` (
  `CONE_VOL_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CONE_VOL_DFNG_SURF_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `VERTEX_POINT_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`CONE_VOL_ID`),
  KEY `IS_THE_VERTEX_FOR` (`VERTEX_POINT_ID`),
  KEY `REF123127` (`CONE_VOL_ID`),
  KEY `IS_USED_TO_DEFINE1` (`CONE_VOL_DFNG_SURF_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_THE_VERTEX_FOR` FOREIGN KEY (`VERTEX_POINT_ID`) REFERENCES `point` (`POINT_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_USED_TO_DEFINE1` FOREIGN KEY (`CONE_VOL_DFNG_SURF_ID`) REFERENCES `surf` (`SURF_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFGEOM_VOL127` FOREIGN KEY (`CONE_VOL_ID`) REFERENCES `geom_vol` (`GEOM_VOL_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `cons_mat_type`;
CREATE TABLE `cons_mat_type` (
  `CONS_MAT_TYPE_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `SUBCAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `HAZARD_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `ISSUING_ELMT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `ISSUING_CNT` decimal(9,0) default NULL,
  `ISSUING_UOM_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `ISSUING_WT_QTY` decimal(12,3) default NULL,
  `PERISHABILITY_IND_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `UNITED_NATIONS_NO_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`CONS_MAT_TYPE_ID`),
  KEY `REF146201` (`CONS_MAT_TYPE_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK285` (`CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK286` (`SUBCAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK287` (`HAZARD_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK288` (`ISSUING_ELMT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK289` (`ISSUING_UOM_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK290` (`PERISHABILITY_IND_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK291` (`UNITED_NATIONS_NO_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK285` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `cons_mat_type_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK286` FOREIGN KEY (`SUBCAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `cons_mat_type_subcat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK287` FOREIGN KEY (`HAZARD_CODE`) REFERENCES `cons_mat_type_hazard_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK288` FOREIGN KEY (`ISSUING_ELMT_CODE`) REFERENCES `cons_mat_type_issuing_elmt_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK289` FOREIGN KEY (`ISSUING_UOM_CODE`) REFERENCES `cons_mat_type_issuing_uom_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK290` FOREIGN KEY (`PERISHABILITY_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `cons_mat_type_perishability_ind_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK291` FOREIGN KEY (`UNITED_NATIONS_NO_CODE`) REFERENCES `cons_mat_type_united_nat_no_cd` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFMAT_TYPE201` FOREIGN KEY (`CONS_MAT_TYPE_ID`) REFERENCES `mat_type` (`MAT_TYPE_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Table structure for table `contxt_assess`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `contxt_assess`;
CREATE TABLE `contxt_assess` (
  `CONTXT_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CONTXT_ASSESS_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `TXT` varchar(2000) NOT NULL,
  `EFFCTV_DTTM` char(18) NOT NULL,
  `ORG_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,

--
-- Table structure for table `fac_type`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `fac_type`;
CREATE TABLE `fac_type` (
  `FAC_TYPE_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`FAC_TYPE_ID`),
  KEY `REF8395` (`FAC_TYPE_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK6` (`CAT_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK6` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `fac_type_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFOBJ_TYPE95` FOREIGN KEY (`FAC_TYPE_ID`) REFERENCES `obj_type` (`OBJ_TYPE_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

-- Dumping data for table `fac_type`

--
-- Table structure for table `fan_area`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `fan_area`;
CREATE TABLE `fan_area` (
  `FAN_AREA_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `MNM_RANGE_DIM` decimal(12,3) NOT NULL,
  `MAX_RANGE_DIM` decimal(12,3) default NULL,
  `ORIENT_ANGLE` decimal(7,4) NOT NULL,
  `SCTR_SIZE_ANGLE` decimal(7,4) NOT NULL,
  `FAN_AREA_VERTEX_POINT_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`FAN_AREA_ID`),
  KEY `REF121122` (`FAN_AREA_ID`),
  KEY `IS_THE_VERTEX_FOR1` (`FAN_AREA_VERTEX_POINT_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_THE_VERTEX_FOR1` FOREIGN KEY (`FAN_AREA_VERTEX_POINT_ID`) REFERENCES `point` (`POINT_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFSURF122` FOREIGN KEY (`FAN_AREA_ID`) REFERENCES `surf` (`SURF_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Table structure for table `met_feat`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `met_feat`;
CREATE TABLE `met_feat` (
  `MET_FEAT_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `INTERPRETATION_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `PROBABILITY_RAT` decimal(6,5) default NULL,
  `SOURCE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `SEVERITY_QUAL_CODE` varchar(6) default NULL,
  `DATE` varchar(8) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`MET_FEAT_ID`),
  KEY `REF143192` (`MET_FEAT_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK233` (`CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK234` (`INTERPRETATION_CODE`),

--
-- Table structure for table `msn_capab`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `msn_capab`;
CREATE TABLE `msn_capab` (
  `MSN_CAPAB_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `LVL_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `QUAL_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `SUBCAT_CODE` varchar(6) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`MSN_CAPAB_ID`),
  KEY `REF77350` (`MSN_CAPAB_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK223` (`CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK224` (`LVL_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK225` (`QUAL_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK223` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `msn_capab_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK224` FOREIGN KEY (`LVL_CODE`) REFERENCES `msn_capab_level_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK225` FOREIGN KEY (`QUAL_CODE`) REFERENCES `msn_capab_qual_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFCAPAB350` FOREIGN KEY (`MSN_CAPAB_ID`) REFERENCES `capab` (`CAPAB_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `msn_capab`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `msn_capab` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `msn_capab` WRITE;
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `msn_capab` ENABLE KEYS */;

--
-- Table structure for table `msn_primacy_code`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `msn_primacy_code`;
CREATE TABLE `msn_primacy_code` (
  `CODE` varchar(6) NOT NULL,
  `DISPLAY_VALUE` varchar(100) default NULL,
  `DEFINITION` text,
  KEY `AA271` (`CODE`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `msn_primacy_code`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `msn_primacy_code` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `msn_primacy_code` WRITE;
INSERT INTO `msn_primacy_code` VALUES ('PRIME','Primary','Denotes the primary mission.'),('SCNDRY','Secondary','Denotes the secondary mission.'),('THIRD','Tertiary','Denotes the tertiary mission.');
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `msn_primacy_code` ENABLE KEYS */;

--
-- Table structure for table `netwrk`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `netwrk`;
CREATE TABLE `netwrk` (
  `NETWRK_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `SUBCAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `ARCH_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CHNL_CNT` decimal(6,0) default NULL,
  `MAX_CAP_QTY` decimal(9,0) default NULL,
  `MNM_CAP_QTY` decimal(9,0) default NULL,
  `MEANS_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CRYPTO_IND_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CRYPTO_PLAN_SHORT_TITLE_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `CRYPTO_CODE_SHORT_TITLE_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `SECURITY_CLSFC_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `SECURITY_CLSFC_CAVEAT_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `SECURITY_POLICY_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `SET_NO_CNT` decimal(6,0) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`NETWRK_ID`),
  KEY `REF97444` (`NETWRK_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK170` (`CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK171` (`SUBCAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK172` (`ARCH_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK173` (`MEANS_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK174` (`CRYPTO_IND_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK175` (`SECURITY_CLSFC_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK176` (`SECURITY_POLICY_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK170` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `netwrk_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK171` FOREIGN KEY (`SUBCAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `netwrk_subcat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK172` FOREIGN KEY (`ARCH_CODE`) REFERENCES `netwrk_arch_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK173` FOREIGN KEY (`MEANS_CODE`) REFERENCES `netwrk_means_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK174` FOREIGN KEY (`CRYPTO_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `netwrk_crypto_ind_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK175` FOREIGN KEY (`SECURITY_CLSFC_CODE`) REFERENCES `security_clsfc_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK176` FOREIGN KEY (`SECURITY_POLICY_CODE`) REFERENCES `netwrk_security_policy_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFFAC444` FOREIGN KEY (`NETWRK_ID`) REFERENCES `fac` (`FAC_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `netwrk`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `netwrk` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `netwrk` WRITE;
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `netwrk` ENABLE KEYS */;

--
-- Table structure for table `netwrk_arch_code`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `netwrk_arch_code`;
CREATE TABLE `netwrk_arch_code` (
  `CODE` varchar(6) NOT NULL,
  `DISPLAY_VALUE` varchar(100) default NULL,
  `DEFINITION` text,
  KEY `AA247` (`CODE`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `netwrk_arch_code`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `netwrk_arch_code` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `netwrk_arch_code` WRITE;
INSERT INTO `netwrk_arch_code` VALUES ('ARCNET','ARCnet','The IEEE 802.4 network architecture.'),('ETHRNT','Ethernet','The IEEE 802.3 (and derivatives) network architecture.'),('MIXED','Mixed','A network where more than one architecture is used.'),('NOS','Not otherwise specified','The appropriate value is not in the set of specified values.'),('TKNRNG','Token ring','The IEEE 802.5 network architecture.'),('WRLESS','Wireless','The IEEE 802.11 network architecture.');
UNLOCK TABLES;

--
-- Table structure for table `nuc_weapon_event`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `nuc_weapon_event`;
CREATE TABLE `nuc_weapon_event` (
  `NUC_WEAPON_EVENT_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `FLASH_TO_BANG_DUR` char(19) default NULL,
  `CRATER_PRSNC_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CRATER_WIDTH_DIM` decimal(12,3) default NULL,
  `YIELD_GROUP_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `YIELD_QTY` decimal(4,0) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`NUC_WEAPON_EVENT_ID`),
  KEY `REF378614` (`NUC_WEAPON_EVENT_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK38` (`CRATER_PRSNC_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK39` (`YIELD_GROUP_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK38` FOREIGN KEY (`CRATER_PRSNC_CODE`) REFERENCES `nuc_wep_event_crtr_prsnc_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK39` FOREIGN KEY (`YIELD_GROUP_CODE`) REFERENCES `nuc_wep_event_yield_group_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFNUC_EVENT614` FOREIGN KEY (`NUC_WEAPON_EVENT_ID`) REFERENCES `nuc_event` (`NUC_EVENT_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `nuc_weapon_event`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `nuc_weapon_event` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `nuc_weapon_event` WRITE;
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `nuc_weapon_event` ENABLE KEYS */;

-- Table structure for table `obj_item`

) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Table structure for table `obj_item_addr`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `obj_item_addr`;
CREATE TABLE `obj_item_addr` (
  `OBJ_ITEM_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `ADDR_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_ITEM_ADDR_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CALL_SIGN_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `PRIMACY_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `AUTH_IND_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `TRNS_RCV_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `NETWRK_ID` decimal(20,0) default NULL,
  `NETWRK_FREQ_IX` decimal(20,0) default NULL,
  `RPTD_ID` decimal(20,0) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`,`ADDR_ID`,`OBJ_ITEM_ADDR_IX`),
  KEY `HAS_FOR_ADDRESS` (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`),
  KEY `PROVIDES_APPLIC_INFO41` (`RPTD_ID`),
  KEY `REF259460` (`ADDR_ID`),
  KEY `IS_ASSIGNED_THROUGH9` (`NETWRK_ID`,`NETWRK_FREQ_IX`),
  KEY `CONFK180` (`AUTH_IND_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK181` (`PRIMACY_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK182` (`TRNS_RCV_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK180` FOREIGN KEY (`AUTH_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `obj_item_addr_auth_ind_cd` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK181` FOREIGN KEY (`PRIMACY_CODE`) REFERENCES `obj_item_addr_prim_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK182` FOREIGN KEY (`TRNS_RCV_CODE`) REFERENCES `obj_item_addr_trns_rcv_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `HAS_FOR_ADDRESS` FOREIGN KEY (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`) REFERENCES `obj_item` (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_ASSIGNED_THROUGH9` FOREIGN KEY (`NETWRK_ID`, `NETWRK_FREQ_IX`) REFERENCES `netwrk_freq` (`NETWRK_ID`, `NETWRK_FREQ_IX`) ON DELETE SET NULL ON UPDATE SET NULL,
  CONSTRAINT `PROVIDES_APPLIC_INFO41` FOREIGN KEY (`RPTD_ID`) REFERENCES `rptd` (`RPTD_ID`) ON DELETE SET NULL ON UPDATE SET NULL,
  CONSTRAINT `REFADDR460` FOREIGN KEY (`ADDR_ID`) REFERENCES `addr` (`ADDR_ID`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

LOCK TABLES `obj_item_addr` WRITE;
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `obj_item_addr` ENABLE KEYS */;

  `SUBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_ITEM_ASSOC_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_ITEM_ASSOC_STAT_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `RPTD_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `ACTIVE_IND_CODE` varchar(6) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`SUBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID`,`OBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID`,`OBJ_ITEM_ASSOC_IX`,`OBJ_ITEM_ASSOC_STAT_IX`),
  KEY `HAS13` (`SUBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID`,`OBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID`,`OBJ_ITEM_ASSOC_IX`),
  KEY `PROVIDES_APPLIC_INFO34` (`RPTD_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK238` (`CAT_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK238` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `assoc_stat_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `HAS13` FOREIGN KEY (`SUBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID`, `OBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID`, `OBJ_ITEM_ASSOC_IX`) REFERENCES `obj_item_assoc` (`SUBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID`, `OBJ_OBJ_ITEM_ID`, `OBJ_ITEM_ASSOC_IX`),
  CONSTRAINT `PROVIDES_APPLIC_INFO34` FOREIGN KEY (`RPTD_ID`) REFERENCES `rptd` (`RPTD_ID`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

-- Table structure for table `obj_item_capab`

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `obj_item_capab`;
CREATE TABLE `obj_item_capab` (
  `OBJ_ITEM_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAPAB_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_ITEM_CAPAB_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `MSN_PRIMACY_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `QTY` decimal(12,3) default NULL,
  `RPTD_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`,`CAPAB_ID`,`OBJ_ITEM_CAPAB_IX`),
  KEY `PROVIDES_APPLIC_INFO8` (`RPTD_ID`),
  KEY `IS_QUANTIFIED_IN2` (`CAPAB_ID`),
  KEY `REF8165` (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK318` (`MSN_PRIMACY_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK318` FOREIGN KEY (`MSN_PRIMACY_CODE`) REFERENCES `msn_primacy_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_QUANTIFIED_IN2` FOREIGN KEY (`CAPAB_ID`) REFERENCES `capab` (`CAPAB_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `PROVIDES_APPLIC_INFO8` FOREIGN KEY (`RPTD_ID`) REFERENCES `rptd` (`RPTD_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFOBJ_ITEM65` FOREIGN KEY (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`) REFERENCES `obj_item` (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

  KEY `REF137438` (`OBJ_REF_OBJ_ITEM_ID`,`OBJ_REF_LOC_ID`,`OBJ_REF_OBJ_ITEM_LOC_IX`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFOBJ_ITEM_LOC438` FOREIGN KEY (`OBJ_REF_OBJ_ITEM_ID`, `OBJ_REF_LOC_ID`, `OBJ_REF_OBJ_ITEM_LOC_IX`) REFERENCES `obj_item_loc` (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`, `LOC_ID`, `OBJ_ITEM_LOC_IX`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFREL_COORD_SYSTEM434` FOREIGN KEY (`REL_COORD_SYSTEM_ID`) REFERENCES `rel_coord_system` (`REL_COORD_SYSTEM_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

  CONSTRAINT `CONFK5` FOREIGN KEY (`DUMMY_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `obj_type_dummy_ind_code` (`CODE`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

  `ESTABD_OBJ_TYPE_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_OBJT_DET_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `MAJOR_PART_IND_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CNT` decimal(9,0) NOT NULL,
  `DET_OBJ_TYPE_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `DET_OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_IX` decimal(20,0) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`ESTABD_OBJ_TYPE_ID`,`OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_IX`,`OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_OBJT_DET_IX`),
  KEY `IS_SPECIFIED_THROUGH1` (`ESTABD_OBJ_TYPE_ID`,`OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_IX`),
  KEY `IDENTIFIES_ESTABLISHMENT_FOR3` (`ESTABD_OBJ_TYPE_ID`,`DET_OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_IX`),
  KEY `REF83528` (`DET_OBJ_TYPE_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK326` (`MAJOR_PART_IND_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK326` FOREIGN KEY (`MAJOR_PART_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `obj_type_estab_objt_det_major_part_ind_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `IDENTIFIES_ESTABLISHMENT_FOR3` FOREIGN KEY (`ESTABD_OBJ_TYPE_ID`, `DET_OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_IX`) REFERENCES `obj_type_estab` (`ESTABD_OBJ_TYPE_ID`, `OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_IX`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_SPECIFIED_THROUGH1` FOREIGN KEY (`ESTABD_OBJ_TYPE_ID`, `OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_IX`) REFERENCES `obj_type_estab` (`ESTABD_OBJ_TYPE_ID`, `OBJ_TYPE_ESTAB_IX`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFOBJ_TYPE528` FOREIGN KEY (`DET_OBJ_TYPE_ID`) REFERENCES `obj_type` (`OBJ_TYPE_ID`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Table structure for table `oig`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `oig`;
CREATE TABLE `oig` (
  `OIG_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`OIG_ID`),
  KEY `REF32585` (`OIG_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK74` (`CAT_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK74` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `oig_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFCONTXT585` FOREIGN KEY (`OIG_ID`) REFERENCES `contxt` (`CONTXT_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `oig`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `oig` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `oig` WRITE;
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `oig` ENABLE KEYS */;

--
-- Table structure for table `oig_cat_code`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `oig_cat_code`;
CREATE TABLE `oig_cat_code` (
  `CODE` varchar(6) NOT NULL,
  `DISPLAY_VALUE` varchar(100) default NULL,
  `DEFINITION` text,
  KEY `AA288` (`CODE`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `oig_cat_code`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `oig_cat_code` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `oig_cat_code` WRITE;
INSERT INTO `oig_cat_code` VALUES ('COMPLN','Composed plan','The specific OPERATIONAL-INFORMATION-GROUP represents all of planning data associated with a given organisation. Planning data from a higher echelon but pertaining to the given organisation may be included as part of this data set.'),('CORENU','Correlated enemy and unknown','The specific OPERATIONAL-INFORMATION-GROUP represents aggregated data about opposing or unknown force elements. Both factual reports and estimates may be included as part of the OPERATIONAL-INFORMATION-GROUP.'),('FRDNEU','Friendly and neutral (organisational)','The specific OPERATIONAL-INFORMATION-GROUP represents essential data about friendly and neutral organisations. The data set includes as a minimum holdings, status, and location.'),('FRNENO','Friendly and neutral (non-organisational)','The specific OPERATIONAL-INFORMATION-GROUP represents data about objects, such as facilities and control measures, that a given organisation controls or is responsible for directly.'),('GLBSGN','Globally significant','The specific OPERATIONAL-INFORMATION-GROUP represents data that cannot be aggregated and does not fall within the scope of other predefined subcategories.'),('UNCORR','Uncorrelated enemy and unknown','The specific OPERATIONAL-INFORMATION-GROUP represents factual data about individual detection or report of opposing or unknown force elements without the data being aggregated.');
UNLOCK TABLES;

--
-- Table structure for table `oig_org_assoc`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `oig_org_assoc`;
CREATE TABLE `oig_org_assoc` (
  `OIG_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,

--
-- Table structure for table `org_stat`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `org_stat`;
CREATE TABLE `org_stat` (
  `ORG_STAT_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `OPERAT_STAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `OPERAT_STAT_QUAL_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `AVLBTY_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CMD_AND_CTRL_ROLE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CMTMNT_STAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `FIRE_MODE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CBRN_DRESS_STATE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `RAD_DOSE_QTY` decimal(6,0) default NULL,
  `RDNS_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `RDNS_DUR` char(19) default NULL,
  `REINFORCE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `RESERVE_IND_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `TRAINING_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `USAGE_STAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `OPERAT_STAT_DET_CODE` varchar(6) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`ORG_STAT_ID`,`OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX`),
  KEY `REF178270` (`ORG_STAT_ID`,`OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX`),
  KEY `CONFK347` (`OPERAT_STAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK348` (`OPERAT_STAT_QUAL_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK349` (`AVLBTY_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK350` (`CMTMNT_STAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK351` (`CMD_AND_CTRL_ROLE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK352` (`FIRE_MODE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK353` (`RDNS_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK354` (`CBRN_DRESS_STATE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK355` (`REINFORCE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK356` (`RESERVE_IND_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK357` (`USAGE_STAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK358` (`TRAINING_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK347` FOREIGN KEY (`OPERAT_STAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_operat_stat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK348` FOREIGN KEY (`OPERAT_STAT_QUAL_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_operat_stat_qual_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK349` FOREIGN KEY (`AVLBTY_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_avlbty_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK350` FOREIGN KEY (`CMTMNT_STAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_cmtmnt_stat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK351` FOREIGN KEY (`CMD_AND_CTRL_ROLE_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_cmd_and_ctrl_role_cd` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK352` FOREIGN KEY (`FIRE_MODE_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_fire_mode_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK353` FOREIGN KEY (`RDNS_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_rdns_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK354` FOREIGN KEY (`CBRN_DRESS_STATE_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_cbrn_dress_state_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK355` FOREIGN KEY (`REINFORCE_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_reinforce_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK356` FOREIGN KEY (`RESERVE_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_reserve_ind_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK357` FOREIGN KEY (`USAGE_STAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_usage_stat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK358` FOREIGN KEY (`TRAINING_CODE`) REFERENCES `org_stat_training_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFOBJ_ITEM_STAT270` FOREIGN KEY (`ORG_STAT_ID`, `OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX`) REFERENCES `obj_item_stat` (`OBJ_ITEM_ID`, `OBJ_ITEM_STAT_IX`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

INSERT INTO `precipitation_cat_code` VALUES ('DRZLE','Drizzle','Fairly uniform precipitation composed exclusively of fine drops (diameter less than 0.02 inch or 0.5 mm) very close together. Drizzle appears to float while following air currents although, unlike fog droplets, it falls to the ground. It usually falls from low stratus clouds and is frequently accompanied by low visibility and fog.'),('FDRZLE','Freezing drizzle','Drizzle which freezes upon impact with the ground, with objects in flight, or with objects on the ground. Produces glaze (clear) ice.'),('FRAIN','Freezing rain','Rain that freezes on impact with the ground, with objects in flight, or with objects on the ground. Produces glaze (clear) ice.'),('HAIL','Hail','Precipitation in the form of small balls or other pieces of ice falling separately or frozen together in irregular lumps. Hailstones consist of alternate opaque and clear layers of ice in most cases. Hail is normally associated with thunderstorms and surface temperatures above freezing.'),('ICECRY','Ice crystals','A fall of unbranched (snow crystals are branched) ice crystals in the form of needles, columns, or plates. They are termed \'ice prisms\' in synoptic observations. Ice crystals are often so tiny they seem to be suspended in air. They may fall from a cloud or from clear air. The crystals are visible mainly when they glitter in the sunshine or other bright light (diamond dust), thus producing a luminous pillar or other optical phenomena. This hydrometer (rarely more than the lightest precipitation), which is frequent in polar regions, occurs only at very low temperatures in stable air masses.'),('ICEPLT','Ice pellets','Precipitation of transparent or translucent pellets of ice, which are round or irregular, rarely conical, and have a diameter of 0.2 inch (5 mm) or less. The pellets usually rebound when striking hard ground and make a sound on impact. There are two main types:  hard grains of ice consisting of frozen raindrops or melted and refrozen snowflakes and pellets of snow encased in a thin layer of ice formed from the freezing, either of droplets intercepted by the pellets, or of water resulting from the partial melting of the pellets.'),('NPR','No precipitation','No measurable precipitation.'),('RAIN','Rain','Precipitation, either in the form of drops larger than 0.02 inch (0.5 mm), or smaller drops, which in contrast to drizzle, are widely separated.'),('RAINSR','Rain shower','The rain changes intensity or starts and stops abruptly. These showers fall exclusively from cumuliform clouds.'),('SLEET','Sleet','A condition with precipitation of rain and snow.'),('SNOW','Snow','Frozen precipitation in the form of white or translucent hexagonal ice crystals that fall in soft, white flakes.'),('SNWGRN','Snow grains','Precipitation of very small, white, opaque particles of ice'),('SNWSHR','Snow shower','Snow changes intensity or starts and stops abruptly. These showers fall exclusively from cumuliform clouds.');
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `precipitation_cat_code` ENABLE KEYS */;

-- Table structure for table `ref`

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `ref`;
CREATE TABLE `ref` (
  `REF_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `APPR_DTTM` char(18) default NULL,
  `CONTENT_CAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CREATION_DTTM` char(18) default NULL,
  `DESCR_TXT` varchar(255) default NULL,
  `ELCTRNC_SOURCE_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `FILE_SIZE_QTY` decimal(9,0) default NULL,
  `FORMAT_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `LANG_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `LIFECYCLE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `MEDIUM_TYPE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `ORIGINATOR_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `PHYSCL_SIZE_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `PRIM_LOC_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `PUBLICATION_DTTM` char(18) default NULL,
  `RELEASABILITY_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `SECURITY_CLSFC_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `SHORT_TITLE_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `TITLE_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `TRANS_TYPE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `VALIDITY_PERIOD_BEGIN_DTTM` char(18) default NULL,
  `VALIDITY_PERIOD_END_DTTM` char(18) default NULL,
  `VERF_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `VERSION_TXT` varchar(50) default NULL,
  `SUFFIX` varchar(10) default NULL,
  `CONTENT_CAT_DET_CODE` varchar(6) default NULL,
  `PLND_EXEC_DTTM` char(18) default NULL,
  `MODIFIED_DTTM` char(18) default NULL,
  `LOC_OF_ISSUE_ID` decimal(20,0) default NULL,
  `TIME_ZONE_CODE` varchar(6) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`REF_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK49` (`SECURITY_CLSFC_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK50` (`CONTENT_CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK51` (`TRANS_TYPE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK52` (`LANG_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK53` (`LIFECYCLE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK54` (`MEDIUM_TYPE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK55` (`VERF_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK49` FOREIGN KEY (`SECURITY_CLSFC_CODE`) REFERENCES `security_clsfc_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK50` FOREIGN KEY (`CONTENT_CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `ref_content_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK51` FOREIGN KEY (`TRANS_TYPE_CODE`) REFERENCES `ref_trans_type_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK52` FOREIGN KEY (`LANG_CODE`) REFERENCES `lang_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK53` FOREIGN KEY (`LIFECYCLE_CODE`) REFERENCES `ref_lifecycle_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK54` FOREIGN KEY (`MEDIUM_TYPE_CODE`) REFERENCES `ref_medium_type_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK55` FOREIGN KEY (`VERF_CODE`) REFERENCES `ref_verf_code` (`CODE`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

Army--An MRR is a temporary flight route recommended for USAF use. It presents the minimum known hazards to low-flying aircraft in the control zone (CZ). The MRR must be approved by the airspace control authority and avoids fire support targets such as air defence weapons, landing zones, pick-up zones, FARPs, and Army airfields.'),('MSR','Main supply route','The route or routes designated with an area of operations on which the bulk of traffic flows in support of military operations.'),('NAVRTE','Area navigation route','An air traffic services route established for the use of aircraft capable of employing area navigation.'),('NKN','Not known','It is not possible to determine which value is most applicable.'),('NOS','Not otherwise specified','The appropriate value is not in the set of specified values.'),('POLRRT','Polar route','Polar route.'),('QROUTE','Q-route','A system of preplanned shipping lanes in mined or potentially mined waters used to minimize the area the mine countermeasures commander has to keep clear of mines in order to provide safe passage for friendly shipping.'),('QRTESG','Q-route-segment','A part of a system of preplanned shipping lanes in mined or potentially mined waters used to minimize the area the mine countermeasures commander has to keep clear of mines in order to provide safe passage for friendly shipping.'),('RETFRT','Return to force route','Planned route profiles for use by friendly aircraft returning to an aircraft-capable ship.'),('RHLNRT','Rhumb line route','The route that maintains a constant direction, shown on a map as a line crossing all meridians at the same angle.'),('SPCCDR','Special corridor','An area established to accommodate the special routing requirements of specific missions.'),('STDART','Standard-use army aircraft flight route','Routes that are established below the coordinating altitude to facilitate the movement of Army aviation assets. Normally, these routes are located in the corps through brigade rear area of operations.'),('STRDRT','Standard route','In air or naval control, a pre-planned single track, assigned with a code name.'),('SUPRRT','Supersonic route','Supersonic route.'),('TACAN','TACAN route','Tactical air navigation route.'),('TMMRRT','Temporary minimum risk route','A temporary route established to route air traffic between transit routes or the rear boundary of the forward area and their operations area in direct support of ground operations.'),('TRNKRT','Trunk route','Trunk route.'),('TRSTRT','Transit route','A temporary corridor of defined dimensions established in the forward area to minimise the risk to friendly aircraft from friendly air defences or surface forces.'),('UNMVRT','Unmanned aerial vehicle route','The CONTROL-FEATURE-TYPE that specifies a route along which an unmanned aerial vehicle travels.'),('USCTRT','Usual coastal route','The route that follows the shape or boundary of a coast.'),('VARTRA','Variable track route','Any combination of other than standard routes.');
UNLOCK TABLES;

--
-- Table structure for table `rptd`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `rptd`;
CREATE TABLE `rptd` (
  `RPTD_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `ACC_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `CNTG_IND_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `CREDIBILITY_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `RELIABILITY_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `REP_DTTM` char(18) NOT NULL,
  `SOURCE_TYPE_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `TIMING_CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `REAL_DATA_EXER_USE_ONLY_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `REF_ID` decimal(20,0) default NULL,
  `REP_ORG_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`RPTD_ID`),
  KEY `IS_THE_REPORTING_AGENT_FOR` (`REP_ORG_ID`),
  KEY `PROVIDES_INFO_RELATED_TO` (`REF_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK56` (`CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK57` (`ACC_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK58` (`CNTG_IND_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK59` (`CREDIBILITY_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK60` (`RELIABILITY_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK61` (`REAL_DATA_EXER_USE_ONLY_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK62` (`SOURCE_TYPE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK63` (`TIMING_CAT_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK56` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `rptd_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK57` FOREIGN KEY (`ACC_CODE`) REFERENCES `rptd_accuracy_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK58` FOREIGN KEY (`CNTG_IND_CODE`) REFERENCES `rptd_cntg_ind_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK59` FOREIGN KEY (`CREDIBILITY_CODE`) REFERENCES `rptd_credibility_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK60` FOREIGN KEY (`RELIABILITY_CODE`) REFERENCES `rptd_reliability_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK61` FOREIGN KEY (`REAL_DATA_EXER_USE_ONLY_CODE`) REFERENCES `rptd_real_data_exr_use_only_cd` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK62` FOREIGN KEY (`SOURCE_TYPE_CODE`) REFERENCES `rptd_source_type_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK63` FOREIGN KEY (`TIMING_CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `rptd_timing_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_THE_REPORTING_AGENT_FOR` FOREIGN KEY (`REP_ORG_ID`) REFERENCES `org` (`ORG_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `PROVIDES_INFO_RELATED_TO` FOREIGN KEY (`REF_ID`) REFERENCES `ref` (`REF_ID`) ON DELETE SET NULL ON UPDATE SET NULL
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Table structure for table `surf_vol`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `surf_vol`;
CREATE TABLE `surf_vol` (
  `SURF_VOL_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `SURF_VOL_DFNG_SURF_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`SURF_VOL_ID`),
  KEY `REF123404` (`SURF_VOL_ID`),
  KEY `IS_USED_TO_DEFINE2` (`SURF_VOL_DFNG_SURF_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_USED_TO_DEFINE2` FOREIGN KEY (`SURF_VOL_DFNG_SURF_ID`) REFERENCES `surf` (`SURF_ID`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFGEOM_VOL404` FOREIGN KEY (`SURF_VOL_ID`) REFERENCES `geom_vol` (`GEOM_VOL_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `surf_vol`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `surf_vol` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `surf_vol` WRITE;
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `surf_vol` ENABLE KEYS */;

--
-- Table structure for table `surface_cat_code`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `surface_cat_code`;
CREATE TABLE `surface_cat_code` (
  `CODE` varchar(6) NOT NULL,
  `DISPLAY_VALUE` varchar(100) default NULL,
  `DEFINITION` text,
  KEY `AA388` (`CODE`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `surface_cat_code`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `surface_cat_code` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `surface_cat_code` WRITE;
INSERT INTO `surface_cat_code` VALUES ('CORDAR','CORRIDOR-AREA','A SURFACE that is defined by its width and a sequence of points.'),('ELLPSE','ELLIPSE','A planar SURFACE in the form of an ellipse.'),('FA','FAN-AREA','A SURFACE that is in the form of a truncated ring sector, which is a sector lying between and being bounded by the rays emanating from the centre-point of the ring and having a central angle.'),('ORBTAR','ORBIT-AREA','An AREA that is (a) an open rectangular section defined by its width and the distance between the two specific POINTS, (b) is closed by two half-circles with radii equal to half the width, and is positioned left, centred, or right with respect to the line formed by the defining points.'),('PLYAAR','POLYARC-AREA','An AREA that consists of a circular arc and a polygonal segment defined by a specific LINE whose beginning coincides with the initial point of the arc and whose end coincides with the last point of the arc.'),('PLYGAR','POLYGON-AREA','An AREA that has its boundaries defined by a specific LINE.'),('TRCKAR','TRACK-AREA','An AREA that is a rectangular section with its length defined by the two specific POINTs and its width by the sum of the widths to the left and right of the connecting line between the two points.');
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `surface_cat_code` ENABLE KEYS */;

--
-- Table structure for table `surv_capab`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `surv_capab`;
CREATE TABLE `surv_capab` (
  `SURV_CAPAB_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`SURV_CAPAB_ID`),
  KEY `REF7757` (`SURV_CAPAB_ID`),

/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `unit` ENABLE KEYS */;

--
-- Table structure for table `unit_type`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `unit_type`;
CREATE TABLE `unit_type` (
  `UNIT_TYPE_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `ARM_CAT_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `ARM_SPCLSN_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `SUPPL_SPCLSN_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `GEN_MOB_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `QUAL_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `SIZE_CODE` char(6) NOT NULL,
  `PRINCIPAL_EQPT_TYPE_ID` decimal(20,0) default NULL,
  `SUPPORTED_MIL_ORG_TYPE_ID` decimal(20,0) default NULL,
  `ECHELON_CODE` varchar(6) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`UNIT_TYPE_ID`),
  KEY `IS_MAIN_EQUIPMENT_OF` (`PRINCIPAL_EQPT_TYPE_ID`),
  KEY `REF252385` (`SUPPORTED_MIL_ORG_TYPE_ID`),
  KEY `REF252386` (`UNIT_TYPE_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK311` (`CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK312` (`ARM_CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK313` (`ARM_SPCLSN_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK314` (`SUPPL_SPCLSN_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK315` (`SIZE_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK316` (`GEN_MOB_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK317` (`QUAL_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK311` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `unit_type_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK312` FOREIGN KEY (`ARM_CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `unit_type_arm_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK313` FOREIGN KEY (`ARM_SPCLSN_CODE`) REFERENCES `unit_type_arm_spclsn_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK314` FOREIGN KEY (`SUPPL_SPCLSN_CODE`) REFERENCES `unit_type_suppl_spclsn_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK315` FOREIGN KEY (`SIZE_CODE`) REFERENCES `unit_type_size_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK316` FOREIGN KEY (`GEN_MOB_CODE`) REFERENCES `unit_type_gen_mob_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK317` FOREIGN KEY (`QUAL_CODE`) REFERENCES `unit_type_qual_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `IS_MAIN_EQUIPMENT_OF` FOREIGN KEY (`PRINCIPAL_EQPT_TYPE_ID`) REFERENCES `eqpt_type` (`EQPT_TYPE_ID`) ON DELETE SET NULL ON UPDATE SET NULL,
  CONSTRAINT `REFMIL_ORG_TYPE385` FOREIGN KEY (`SUPPORTED_MIL_ORG_TYPE_ID`) REFERENCES `mil_org_type` (`MIL_ORG_TYPE_ID`) ON DELETE SET NULL ON UPDATE SET NULL,
  CONSTRAINT `REFMIL_ORG_TYPE386` FOREIGN KEY (`UNIT_TYPE_ID`) REFERENCES `mil_org_type` (`MIL_ORG_TYPE_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Table structure for table `wind`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `wind`;
CREATE TABLE `wind` (
  `WIND_ID` decimal(20,0) NOT NULL,
  `CAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `AIR_STABILITY_CAT_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `ALTITUDE_LAYER_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `DIR_ANGLE` decimal(7,4) default NULL,
  `EFFCTV_DOWNWIND_DIR_ANGLE` decimal(7,4) default NULL,
  `SPEED_RATE` decimal(8,4) default NULL,
  `NUC_YIELD_QUAL_CODE` char(6) default NULL,
  `SPEED_MIN` decimal(8,4) default NULL,
  `SPEED_MAX` decimal(8,4) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`WIND_ID`),
  KEY `REF131142` (`WIND_ID`),
  KEY `CONFK266` (`CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK267` (`AIR_STABILITY_CAT_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK268` (`ALTITUDE_LAYER_CODE`),
  KEY `CONFK269` (`NUC_YIELD_QUAL_CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK266` FOREIGN KEY (`CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `wind_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK267` FOREIGN KEY (`AIR_STABILITY_CAT_CODE`) REFERENCES `wind_air_stability_cat_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK268` FOREIGN KEY (`ALTITUDE_LAYER_CODE`) REFERENCES `wind_altitude_layer_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `CONFK269` FOREIGN KEY (`NUC_YIELD_QUAL_CODE`) REFERENCES `wind_nuc_yield_qual_code` (`CODE`),
  CONSTRAINT `REFMET_FEAT142` FOREIGN KEY (`WIND_ID`) REFERENCES `met_feat` (`MET_FEAT_ID`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

--
-- Dumping data for table `wind`
--


/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `wind` DISABLE KEYS */;
LOCK TABLES `wind` WRITE;
UNLOCK TABLES;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `wind` ENABLE KEYS */;
